The paper discusses deep learning and representation learning, which are core topics in machine learning. The focus is on learning representations from both big and small data, which suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories. However, given the emphasis on deep learning and representation learning, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses CNN model enhancements for representation learning, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well. Additionally, the paper discusses transfer representation learning, which is a common technique in both cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper mentions the scale of computation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
